sp., det. T. Huddleston, 1982&quot;. Paratypes (2 ♀ + 1 ♂): 1 ♀ (RMNH), &quot;England: Hants., New Forest, Minstead, 5.viii.[19]63. In cage with 
<taxonomicName id="5CE408771CCDEAC8720B2B690F9FCAE0" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1767" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Apatele" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis id="1352FC108CCA3B4395AE3B4EA2B2F51A" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Apatele alni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, L.W. Siggs&quot;, &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="BCA324E000AA91BE375A49E566DD4250" authorityName="Agassiz" authorityYear="1846" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aspidogonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="40AC92FFCD945121AB461187E3A3CB04" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Aspidogonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., R.D. Eady det. 1967&quot;; 1 ♀ + 1 ♂ (BMNH), &quot;D. [= Germany], [near] Freiburg, Bechtaler Wald [= a strictly protected forest reserve near Weisweil in 
<normalizedToken id="F3CA52E0DC66E46375A66284ED8EFA9B" originalValue="Baden-Württemberg">Baden-Wuerttemberg</normalizedToken>
], 1996&quot;, &quot;ex 
<taxonomicName id="0C8742DF7F83100AA69B1C05DB6FC2F9" class="Insecta" family="Anobiidae" genus="Ptilinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pecticornis">
<emphasis id="22794B5A419C21BBD4AEBF3EC425185E" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Ptilinus pecticornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;, &quot;Hedqvist coll. BMNH(E) 2011-27&quot;.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="284F6512078B6298F139583A4C0B123D" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="96" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="AC73446D1B495FD6E88522482CBC798F" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4E8421A9C5FC5F4C294A36B5F3CB30AE" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="96" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">
Clypeus with small acute tooth medio-ventrally (
<figureCitation id="1316104F23F7A72B1C70B790659AE768" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); face 4.0 times wider than high medially and with separate triangular area medially (
<figureCitation id="60D9B0F5A7DEEFF6378DF9DFFC56CDBE" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); 
<pageBreakToken id="55CEE11F097362C4C7E20C8D1FC86181" pageId="4" pageNumber="95" start="start">frons</pageBreakToken>
largely coriaceous (
<figureCitation id="7BC321BC721449AEB71B7179B073C9AF" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">Figs 5, 6</figureCitation>
); malar suture present, except dorsal third (
<figureCitation id="9FA4BEB92B34355F83821EC5DD6D8726" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); hind coxa largely rugose dorsally (
<figureCitation id="BD61F3298B610DF07779E380F8A7E960" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); mesosoma black or dark brown; length of first tergite about twice its apical width (
<figureCitation id="A86E5EF31EB06077066AB82D019C055D" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); length of ovipositor sheath 
<pageBreakToken id="5712240E0F953DF1178158F2EA92E3ED" pageId="5" pageNumber="96" start="start">1.2</pageBreakToken>
-1.3 times as long as fore wing (
<figureCitation id="7D1DEAAEA5882B7AF0E1C44E30DD3BF9" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Figs 1, 14</figureCitation>
); length of fore wing 3.6-4.2 mm; antenna with 27-30 segments.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="70AEDCFD46FAF6EE682ADEA43CE05481" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="97" pageId="5" pageNumber="96" type="description">
<paragraph id="2A246434CC7ABE70F778880C22B6996B" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E6412351B0D1C6D583CE729C8B4055E" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Holotype, ♀, length of body 5.0 mm, of fore wing 4.2 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="190BABF5EC1A35174F8F88F62D3DC23F" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis id="6A3DBA646173557269E13AD181974914" bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Head.</emphasis>
Antenna with 28 segments and 1.1 times as long as fore wing (
<figureCitation id="3221608F844CEF6F7E31312F13AAD952" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
); third segment 0.9 times as long as fourth segment, length of third, fourth and penultimate segments 3.6, 4.0 and 1.3 times their width, respectively; length of maxillary palp nearly equal to height of head; third segment of maxillary palp distinctly widened medially; second segment of labial palp wide, triangular with fourth segment inserted at lower corner (
<figureCitation id="7240773A163801A9F31922BE8CF156F1" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
); occipital carina complete but medio-dorsally weakly developed; hypostomal carina narrow; length of eye in dorsal view 1.5 times temple (
<figureCitation id="1355172B2B7E64C2EA687CEAE0EF7DB8" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); frons moderately depressed and coriaceous medially, without median carina or groove and laterally slightly convex and punctate; face 4.0 times wider than high, slightly convex and punctate laterally and medially with triangular flat area (
<figureCitation id="5C40CCD4DE4E0B82AA1ABC036201DFA4" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); clypeus convex and sparsely but distinctly punctate, its ventral margin thick and medio-ventrally with small tooth (
<figureCitation id="ED32A9310AB4FE19D3E13E78D754535C" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); malar suture present, except dorsal 0.3 of malar space, malar space 1.2 times as long as basal width of mandible (
<figureCitation id="804544F56B53BC443E8C9FE61B5C4F13" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
); mandible with deep transverse groove basally (
<figureCitation id="D70194539F43BD268F03C5F0BE162B4E" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), ventral tooth about as wide as longer dorsal tooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EAA21B1C9997F71300AC4E2562EC7065" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis id="AB08A9E2BB66B4A62760F95F160A20C7" bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
Length of mesosoma 1.5 times its height; dorsal pronope wide and moderately impressed, with pronotum truncate anteriorly (
<figureCitation id="56A94E64616B7FE4D7540660A1776940" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); antescutal depression absent, but with triangular flat area; pronotal sides largely punctate-rugose and medially crenulate; epicnemial area and complete precoxal sulcus widely reticulate-rugose and rest of mesopleuron (except dorsally) largely smooth; pleural sulcus crenulate; mesosternal sulcus wide and coarsely crenulate; notauli complete, crenulate and posteriorly wide (
<figureCitation id="BBF88A7DFE859733C9912A9FFE473FE2" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); middle lobe of mesoscutum densely punctate and posteriorly rugose, with a median carina, both lateral lobes largely smooth (
<figureCitation id="83083640F4B2337205E7FD8B5AAA413B" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); scutellar sulcus deep, wide and with irregular carinae; scutellum punctate and convex medially, with paired depressions medio-posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="F474AB193E4EE189957337ADD1CD8B08" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); surface of propodeum densely and coarsely rugose but anteriorly smooth, median carina short, posterior face hardly separated from dorsal face, lateral tubercles indistinct and areola absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="90C1F707A1B3551A831F1C75DEA56A86" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis id="31C6E05399836547B9C4C2A0C73B7412" bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Wings.</emphasis>
Fore wing (
<figureCitation id="5DD47354543357B1E1BFB46DBA0B00C3" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
): pterostigma triangular; first discal cell narrowly truncate anteriorly; 1-R1 ending before wing apex and 1.3 times as long as pterostigma; r:3-SR:SR1 = 9:13:74; 2-SR:3-SR:r-m = 28:13:22; 2-M nearly twice as long as 3-SR; r slender; 1-M and SR1 straight; cu-a interstitial; first subdiscal cell closed, CU1b short; M+CU1 sclerotized. Hind wing: M+CU:1-M = 24:15; cu-a straight.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EAAEAD1E2DA03919FA2E8E331B7C1E1B" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis id="0C7E973ACDD2C6500C2BD6ED8D9AB313" bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Legs.</emphasis>
Hind coxa densely rugose dorsally (
<figureCitation id="735DD1BDA82E535E00AB4BDE9083FD09" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Figs 7, 13</figureCitation>
); length of femur, tibia and basitarsus of hind leg 4.2, 8.7 and 8.4 times as long as wide, respectively; hind femur largely smooth; hind tibia slightly narrowed apically (
<figureCitation id="28261A52EEAB320D53E43D6436448E5D" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); hind tibial spurs slender, apically acute and both 0.3 times as long as basitarsus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6F93D81D2CED543D1B5668894906A7C9" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="97" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis id="18EE158FA73949B195E6EE0B6ECE1CBE" bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Metasoma</emphasis>
. First tergite 2.1 times as long as its apical width, surface largely rugose with straight dorsal carinae on basal 0.3 of tergite (
<figureCitation id="43D99A7649B944354799A4CA4A3AF242" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); second suture absent; second and following tergites smooth; length of setose part of ovipositor sheath 1.18 
<pageBreakToken id="D6E009F86C7F805974EB0ADB53ED8F38" pageId="6" pageNumber="97" start="start">times</pageBreakToken>
fore wing; upper valve of ovipositor depressed apically, without apical notch or nodus (
<figureCitation id="96EB0147F1334C16ABC485C42C9BA3F5" captionStart="Figures 1–16" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 16. Vadumasonium vardyorum sp. n., ♀, holotype, but 9 and 16 of holotype of Vadumasonium volatum (Mason), ♀. 1 wings 2 mesosoma dorsal 3 apex of antenna 4 first-third metasomal tergites dorsal 5 head frontal 6 head dorsal 7 hind leg lateral 8 detail of fore wing postero-basally 9 first tergite dorsal 10 antenna 11 base of antenna 12 inner hind claw 13 habitus lateral 14 ovipositor 15 apex of ovipositor lateral 16 clypeus frontal. 1, 7, 10, 13, 14: scale-line (= 1.0 x); 2, 4 - 7: 1.7 x; 3: 2.5 x; 8, 9, 16: 2.0 x; 11, 12, 15: 5.0 x." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11773" pageId="6" pageNumber="97">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); hypopygium truncate apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0DC535274773E814EA92778773F0E690" pageId="6" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="343C75A6B531AB7AE005EB8DC4B36059" bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="97">Colour.</emphasis>
Black; antenna, clypeus, hind leg (but trochanter and trochantellus yellow), metasoma (but baso-ventrally yellowish-brown), pterostigma, parastigma and ovipositor sheath dark brown; remainder of legs (but middle coxa largely dark brown) and mandible brownish-yellow; veins brown; palpi, trochanters and trochantelli pale yellow; wing membrane slightly infuscate but somewhat darker near vein r of fore wing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="22A350A2D8B2256BB06D439552E9505C" pageId="6" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="E0A7C4E4B9EF72A7A7C65A32CCE195E3" bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="97">Male.</emphasis>
The males do not differ from the females except for the sexual differences and a slightly higher number of antennal segments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CBD6190BE974A0E641E905888C582D4F" pageId="6" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="F238727F1B09C4F0FC6CC247D92F88CD" bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="97">Variation.</emphasis>
Length of body 5.0-5.3 mm, fore wing 3.6-4.2 mm; antenna of female with 27 (1) or 28 (1) segments and of male 30 (1); first tergite 1.9-2.2 times as long as its apical width; ovipositor sheath 1.18-1.31 times as long as fore wing; vein cu-a of fore wing interstitial or narrowly postfurcal; frons with or without an irregular median carina; second tergite smooth or with some obsolescent sculpture basally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2CD63A1F62C15B81782A941CFB5F75B1" pageId="6" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="BC26B573BB31A8808A80D6131E21CE84" bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="97">Biology.</emphasis>
Reared from 
<taxonomicName id="1FEA9DD3B7B1A89F02333847D38FCED3" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Anobiidae" genus="Ptilinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinicornis">
<emphasis id="A69C7C8AC3F20B1400BACA9D9277710B" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="97">Ptilinus pectinicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Linnaeus, 1758) (
<taxonomicName id="CDA95291716D63B0302A4543CBA9F60C" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Coleoptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="D4761FC2F8ABCF69DC5011523C7E1FBF" class="Insecta" family="Anobiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Anobiidae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="36B9209074B0B2F3F18E42B8DA4BA7A1" lsidName="" pageId="6" pageNumber="97" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ptilininae">Ptilininae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="349F00B29722BBFA7489D8449D02D118" pageId="6" pageNumber="97" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0B11DE468692324BD3E0179C0744E439" pageId="6" pageNumber="97">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A596E40711C4DA0C9A2F5C44A722FCBC" pageId="6" pageNumber="97">England, Germany.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9577EE007CD5B52E764AE12AE0D05C4A" pageId="6" pageNumber="97" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E698F4018978000AF8495B9B27BD3091" pageId="6" pageNumber="97">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="38CD468D73F5984CD44D63F026C78501" pageId="6" pageNumber="97">Named after Colin and Martha Vardy, for collecting the holotype and for their hospitality during visits by the senior author.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
